[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: E, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 0, nRot: 1, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "43f8c4a406268d724ec0f1af308c7b479b5154c8e49b907a2c54dd48cea5fe15"]
[Category "Competitive Bidding"]
[Difficulty "beginner"]
[SkillPath "competitive_bidding/takeout_doubles"]
[Student "S"]
{The bidding has been as shown.   

Partner told you to bid, so you say 2\C. North repeats his suit and partner then says 2\S.  

By doubling and then bidding his own suit, partner is showing a good hand, at least 17 points. Your hand can be revalued to about 7 points so you are good enough to invite partner to game. You bid 3\S and partner says 4\S.}

